Preconditions:
The input array `arr` must not be null.
The input array `arr` must contain exactly 4 elements.
The elements in the input array `arr` must be integers.
The integers in the input array `arr` must be between 0 and 9 (inclusive).

Postconditions:
The method should return a string in the format `"HH:MM"`.
The returned string should represent the latest 24-hour time that can be formed using the elements in the input array `arr`.
If no valid time can be formed, the method should return an empty string.